## ARDUINO IDE SETUP

### 1. Add ESP32S3 Board Support
File → Preferences → Additional Board Manager URLs:
  https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json

Tools → Board Manager → Search "esp32" → Install (Espressif Systems)

### 2. Select Board
Tools → Board → ESP32S3 Dev Module
  (or search "XIAO ESP32S3" if listed)

Board Settings:
  USB CDC On Boot: Enabled
  Flash Size:      8MB (or match your board)
  Partition Scheme: Default 4MB with spiffs

### 3. Install Libraries
Tools → Manage Libraries:
  - "NimBLE-Arduino" by h2zero  ← IMPORTANT: use NimBLE, not ESP32 BLE Arduino

### 4. Flash
Select correct COM port → Upload vaani_node.ino

### 5. Tune WAKE_THRESHOLD
Open Serial Monitor (115200 baud).
Speak normally — watch the amplitude values printed.
Adjust WAKE_THRESHOLD in the .ino:
  Too many false triggers → increase (e.g., 2000)
  Doesn't trigger on speech → decrease (e.g., 800)

